xt Generation]]'', which he starred on from 2010 to 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.postcity.com/Eat-Shop-Do/Do/July-2015/Luke-Bilyk-looks-back-on-life-as-a-Degrassi-star/|title=Luke Bilyk looks back on life as a Degrassi star|website=www.postcity.com|access-date=June 17, 2016}}</ref> He's also appeared in film roles such as TJ in ''[[F the Prom]]'' (2017).\n\n== Early life ==\nBilyk grew up in [[Vaughan|Vaughan, Ontario]] with three older sisters. He is of Italian, Ukrainian, German, and Jewish descent.<ref>https://www.lukebilyk.ca/about-me/biography</ref> Bilyk attended [[St. Elizabeth Catholic High School]] in Thornhill, where he was part of the Regional Arts Program for Drama.{{cn|date=September 2019}}\n\n== Career ==\n{{Expand section|date=October 2016}}Bilyk had a recurring role as Mark in season 5 of ''[[Lost Girl]]''.{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Gooby]]''\n| Cute Kid\n| Film Debut, Movie Debut\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Hellions (film)|Hellions]]''\n| Jace\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=3| 2017\n| ''Kiss and Cry''\n| John Servinis\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Adam's Testament]]''\n| Adam Gable\n|\n|-\n| ''[[F the Prom]]''\n| TJ\n| \n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Black Conflux]]''\n| Donovan\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Little Mosque on the Prairie]]''\n| Halaqa Teen #1\n| \"Best Intentions\" (Season 2, Episode 7 )\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[The Latest Buzz]]''\n| Teenager\n| \"The Showdown Issue\" (Season 2, Episode 6)\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[The Jon Dore Television Show]]''\n| Skateboard Kid #2\n| \"Jon Gets Old\" (Season 2, Episode 3)\n|-\n| 2010-2015\n| ''[[Degrassi: The Next Generation|Degrassi]]''\n| Andrew \"Drew\" Torres\n| Main Cast (seasons 10-14)\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[My Babysitter's a Vampire]]''\n| The Seeker\n|  TV Movie\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Flashpoint 